The paper introduces a new algorithm for recurrent neural networks, which is relevant to the fields of neural networks and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also presents experimental results on synthetic problems and character-level language modelling, which suggests that it could be relevant to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
